Days after being kidnapped, Plateau State Commissioner for Environment, Usman Bamaiyi’s wife and daughter have regained their freedom from the hands of their abductors. Usman Bamaiyi, the Plateau State Commissioner for Environment’s wife and daughter were abducted when terrorists stormed the Commissioner’s residence located in Gindiri community, Mangu Local Government Area of the State in the early hours of Saturday, 9th April 2022. Daily Post reports that a source in the Gindiri community said they have been released to the family. According to the source, “The two kidnapped victims regained their freedom on Monday night.”